    &lt;Title&gt;Great care to keep me alive&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I was admitted to intensive care and HDU in Musgrove Park Hospital several times over the past few months, and would like like thank the dedicated and professional staff who kept me alive from the massive overdoses I had taken when very unwell in my mind.
I had complications and they looked after me well back to physically and medically able to leave hospital again.
The only thing which I cannot get to grips with is, they are quite happy to discharge you with no mental health support whatsoever so I have had to keep using critical care time and time again. Not only does it cost hughly to the NHSin terms of money and staff,  but it does not do me any good as I have been told my body cannot take much more.  Surely if Musgrove Park Hospital were to help me with my mental health I would not have to keep using critical care beds and be on life support time and time again. 
It is not a complete service pathway. Its false economy. And the costs to my quality of life is not a good outcome. Mph does not seem to understand that if my mind was given the therapy it really needs it would cut my visits to high cost units. 
&lt;/CommentText&gt;
